# Chapter 3: Creating your Kiwix Archive
## introduciton: 
There will no doubt come a point when you will need to access knowledge that is otherwise unavailable in this manual, or the Linux MAN Pages. As well as 
this, there will no doubt come a point where maybe you'll need to know: "is this plant poisonous?" or "How do I do CPR?" or "How many quarts in one gallon?". In this case, Kiwix will come to your aid. Kiwix is a program that can download offline copies of various wikimedia projects, usually in the form of ".zim" files. 
